Investor publishes Annual report 2025
Today, Investor publishes the Annual report 2025, including the Sustainability report, outlining our continued focus on long-term value creation through Performance, Portfolio and People.

Investor’s portfolio companies performed strongly in 2025, resulting in adjusted net asset value growth of 14 percent and a total shareholder return of 15 percent. During the year, the portfolio also delivered on its 2030 sustainability target, reducing scope 1 and 2 emissions by 74 percent compared with the 2016 base year.

In the Annual Report, Chair of the Board Jacob Wallenberg describes a new world order marked by complexity and unpredictability—and this new reality calls for decisive action – from all of us, from our companies, and across Sweden, the Nordics and Europe.

“Investor, and the companies in which we are owners, have stayed focused on what truly matters: performance, long-term value creation, and the ability to seize opportunities even in these turbulent times”, says Jacob Wallenberg.

“I am proud to see how our companies managed this environment with determination – protecting profits here and now, while continuing to invest in innovation and product development, AI and other new technologies, as well as the green transition – all with the goal to strengthen long-term competitiveness and customer value”,  says Christian Cederholm in his CEO statement.

Read more about our focus on the future and long-term value creation in the Annual Report 2025 on www.investorab.com

